===Strings===
Data type used to represent textual data.They are sequences of characters and are enclosed in either.
single quotes('')
double quotes("")
triple quotes("' "' or """ """)
===how to create string===
you can create strings using single,double,triple quotes.Triple quotes are used for multiline strings or to include special characters like line breaks.
single_quotes='Hello world'
double_quotes="Hello world"
multiline ="'Hello,
             world!
             Welcome"'
===string indexing===
string are ordered sequences,and you can access individual characters using indexing.python uses zero-based indexing where the first character has an index of o.
ex:--str = "PYTHON"
print(str[0])          
print(str[2])
print(str[-1])
print(str[4])
output:---P
T
N
O
